TY  - JOUR
T1  - Shared Storage Policies Based on the Duration Stay of Unit Loads
AU  - Goetschalckx, Marc
AU  - Ratliff, H. Donald
Y1  - 1990/09/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.36.9.1120
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.36.9.1120
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1120
EP  - 1132
VL  - 36
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper addresses duration-of-stay-based shared storage policies for a unit load warehouse. We show that, for single command storage and retrieval, shared storage policies based on duration of stay of individual unit loads have the potential to significantly decrease travel time. An optimal storage policy with respect to travel time and storage space is developed for systems with balanced input and output. Based on the same principles, two heuristic policies are developed for more complex systems. Simulation results are provided which compare travel times for dedicated storage, random storage, turnover-based storage classes, and duration-of-stay-based storage classes.
AB  - This paper addresses duration-of-stay-based shared storage policies for a unit load warehouse. We show that, for single command storage and retrieval, shared storage policies based on duration of stay of individual unit loads have the potential to significantly decrease travel time. An optimal storage policy with respect to travel time and storage space is developed for systems with balanced input and output. Based on the same principles, two heuristic policies are developed for more complex systems. Simulation results are provided which compare travel times for dedicated storage, random storage, turnover-based storage classes, and duration-of-stay-based storage classes.
